<TITLE> BB hunts account info on Rokanuddin, Joy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 2 (bdnews24.com) -- Bangladesh Bank has asked banks to send account information of 199 people, including Sheikh Hasina's son Sajeeb Wazed Joy, a senior official said Thursday. The central bank also asked the commercial banks to send account information about Supreme Court lawyer Rokanuddin Mahmud by August 5. The banks face the August 8 deadline for the remaining 198 people. "We have asked banks to check whether those people have any account," the official with the central bank told bdnews24.com, asking not to be named. Former BNP lawmaker Mosaddek Ali Falu, Jamuna Group chairman Nurul Islam Babul, controversial businessman Gaisuddin Al Mamun, and former Awami League minister Mohammad Nasim are among others. b
